{"questionId":"5275192","questionHtml":"<p>An electron is accelerated from rest through a potential difference <em>V</em>.</p>\n<p>What is the maximum speed of the electron?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>e</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><msub><mi>m</mi><mi>e</mi></msub></mfrac></msqrt></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><msub><mi>m</mi><mi>e</mi></msub></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>e</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><msub><mi>m</mi><mi>e</mi></msub></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>V</mi></mrow><msub><mi>m</mi><mi>e</mi></msub></mfrac></msqrt></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"5275192","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ2.22","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"An electron is accelerated from rest through a potential difference V. What is the maximum speed of the electron? A. 2eVme B. eVme C. 2eVme D. 2Vme","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"22","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)","A.1 – The beginnings of relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","5.4 – Magnetic effects of electric currents","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}